<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-87-0992 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book presents the case for an energy future based on renewable energysources rather than one dominated by coal and nuclear power. It is dividedinto 9 chapters with the following headings: the energy debate: moredivergence than consensus; the US energy conservation-efficiency potential;renewable energy in the United States; state, regional, and local issues;what of coal, synfuels, and nuclear power?; other industrial nations;third world energy futures; some notes on the transition; getting therefrom here; some policy proposals</TEXT></DOC>